cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.CR

This paper deals with the task of identifying comments that violate community norms on Reddit, which falls under the domain of natural language processing and computational social science. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves classification and topic modeling techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning and data mining research, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with issues related to online moderation and community guidelines, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
